EMS-RC-101	Awareness and Training Policy	The organization develops, documents, and disseminates a security awareness and training policy that addresses purpose, scope, roles, responsibilities, management commitment, and coordination. Policy is reviewed and updated annually.
EMS-RC-102	Continuous Monitoring	The organization continuously monitors information systems and assets to identify cybersecurity events and verify the effectiveness of protective measures. Monitoring coverage spans network, endpoint, and cloud surfaces.
EMS-RC-103	Response Planning	The organization develops, documents, and disseminates an incident response plan that addresses identification, containment, eradication, recovery, and lessons learned. Plan is reviewed and tested annually.
EMS-RC-104	Data Protection at Rest	The organization protects the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data at rest through encryption, access controls, and integrity verification. Key management follows approved standards.
EMS-RC-105	Risk Assessment Program	The organization conducts risk assessments of information systems and processes annually or upon material change. Assessments identify threats, vulnerabilities, likelihood, and impact, and inform risk treatment decisions.
EMS-RC-106	Information Protection Processes	The organization establishes and maintains processes that protect organizational information assets including configuration management, secure baseline maintenance, and protection of system documentation.



